# MeetMatch Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .dev.vars (for Cloudflare Workers) or .env as needed

# ============================================
# BOT CONFIGURATION
# ============================================

# Required: Telegram Bot Token (get from @BotFather: https://t.me/BotFather)
BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token_here

# Optional: Telegram webhook secret token for verifying requests
# TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here

# Optional: Admin Telegram chat ID for error reports and notifications
# ADMIN_CHAT_ID=123456789

# ============================================
# OBSERVABILITY (Cloudflare OpenTelemetry Export)
# ============================================
#
# Error tracking and tracing are handled natively by Cloudflare Workers
# via OpenTelemetry export. No SDK or env vars needed here.
#
# To set up:
# 1. Go to Cloudflare Dashboard → Workers & Pages → Observability
# 2. Add a destination (Sentry, Honeycomb, Datadog, etc.)
# 3. Uncomment the destinations in wrangler.toml
# 4. Redeploy
#
# Supported providers: Sentry, Honeycomb, Grafana, Axiom, Firetiger,
# New Relic, Splunk, and any OTLP-compatible backend.
